---
import BaseLayout from '@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import TrialCTA from '@/components/TrialCTA.astro';
import { siteConfig } from '@/config/site';

const title = 'Trust tools for coaches, consultants and L&D practitioners';
const description = 'Trust Leader gives practitioners a Trust Map, approved Behaviour Playlists, between-session practice and dated evidence for work with clients.';
---

<BaseLayout title={`${title} — Trust Leader`} description={description} pageClass="practitioner-page">
  <header class="page-hero page-hero--practitioners">
    <div class="shell page-hero__grid">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">For practitioners</p>
        <h1>Keep your judgement at the centre. Give the work more structure.</h1>
        <p class="lede">You bring the client, the judgement and the relationship. Trust Leader gives the work a map, approved behaviour practice between conversations and evidence you can review together.</p>
        <div class="hero__actions">
          <a class="button button--green" href={siteConfig.trialUrl} data-analytics="start_trial">Start your 28-day free trial</a>
          <a class="button button--outline" href="/how-it-works/">See how it works</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="practitioner-proof practitioner-proof--hero" aria-label="Trust Leader keeps practitioner judgement central while adding structure, practice and evidence">
        <div class="practitioner-proof__centre"><span>Practitioner</span><strong>Your judgement</strong><small>stays central</small></div>
        <ol>
          <li><span>01</span><strong>Structure</strong><small>Five Trust Questions.</small></li>
          <li><span>02</span><strong>Practice</strong><small>Behaviour in real work.</small></li>
          <li><span>03</span><strong>Evidence</strong><small>Dated reflection and review.</small></li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="section section--paper">
    <div class="shell problem-grid">
      <div><p class="eyebrow">The gap it closes</p><h2>Trust comes up in the room. Then the session ends.</h2></div>
      <div><p>Trust sits beneath many coaching, consulting and L&D conversations. A client is capable but not backed. A team completes the work but stays silent. A relationship keeps producing surprises.</p><p>You can name the issue. The difficult part is giving the person something specific to do before the next conversation, then finding evidence of what changed.</p><p>Trust Leader connects those two moments.</p></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--navy" aria-labelledby="practitioner-value-heading">
    <div class="shell">
      <div class="section-heading"><div><p class="eyebrow eyebrow--light">What it adds</p><h2 id="practitioner-value-heading">Structure, practice and evidence.</h2></div><p>The platform handles the repeatable parts. The judgement, challenge and relationship remain yours.</p></div>
      <div class="value-columns">
        <article><span>01</span><h3>Structure</h3><p>Five Trust Questions and focused behaviours give the trust conversation a shared language without reducing the person to a type or score.</p></article>
        <article><span>02</span><h3>Practice</h3><p>Short activities help clients act in the real relationship between conversations, where confidence is actually formed.</p></article>
        <article><span>03</span><h3>Evidence</h3><p>Dated maps, activity records, shared reflections and private journal entries give the client something specific to review and decide from.</p></article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="shell practitioner-use-grid">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Use it without becoming it</p>
        <h2>Trust Leader supports your approach. It does not replace it.</h2>
        <p>The platform is good at providing a consistent structure, approved Behaviour Playlists and a dated record. It cannot make the judgement a practitioner makes about the person, situation and pace.</p>
        <p>Activity reflections are shared with you by default, while journal entries start private. Your client can change that choice and remains in control of what they share. That keeps the platform useful without turning the relationship into monitoring.</p>
      </div>
      <ul class="practice-outcomes">
        <li><strong>Coaches</strong><span>Give trust work a practical thread between sessions.</span></li>
        <li><strong>Consultants</strong><span>Connect a behaviour framework to real organisational work.</span></li>
        <li><strong>L&amp;D and OD</strong><span>Add practice and evidence to programmes already in place.</span></li>
        <li><strong>Small providers</strong><span>Offer a structured client experience without building a platform.</span></li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--green">
    <div class="shell growth-grid">
      <div><p class="eyebrow">Start small, then grow</p><h2>Use the platform at the level your practice needs.</h2></div>
      <div class="growth-steps">
        <article><span>Trial</span><h3>Test one real relationship.</h3><p>28 days, no credit card and no automatic subscription.</p><a class="text-link" href={siteConfig.trialUrl} data-analytics="start_trial">Start free</a></article>
        <article><span>Practitioner</span><h3>Work with your own clients.</h3><p>£75 a month or £750 a year with five client seats. Your Practitioner account does not use a seat.</p><a class="text-link" href="/pricing/">See pricing</a></article>
        <article><span>Certified Practitioner</span><h3>Create custom Behaviour Playlists.</h3><p>A separate pathway with 50 places in the founding cohort. Certification is not open for direct purchase.</p><a class="text-link" href={siteConfig.certifiedWaitlistUrl}>Join the Certified Practitioner waitlist</a></article>
        <article><span>Partner</span><h3>Run a larger programme.</h3><p>For consultancies, providers and organisation-wide use.</p><a class="text-link" href="/contact/?topic=partnership">Talk to us</a></article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section"><div class="shell"><TrialCTA text="28 days free. No card. Decide by using it with a real situation." /></div></section>
</BaseLayout>
